conception /kənˈsɛpʃən/

(conceptions) 

1. N-VAR A conception of something is an idea that you have of it in your mind. (对某事物的) 概念 

例： My conception of a garden was based on gardens I had visited in England. 我对花园的概念是基于我在英格兰参观过的一些花园的。 

2. N-VAR Conception is the process in which the egg in a woman is fertilized and she becomes pregnant. 受孕 

例： Six weeks after conception, your baby is the size of your little fingernail. 受孕六周后你的孩子有你小手指甲那么大。

